cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper is about visual object tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel approach that involves training a distance learning network, which falls under the category of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed tracker is also designed to run in real-time, which involves considerations of robotics and control, cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed tracker on benchmark datasets, which falls under the category of multimedia, cs.MM (Multimedia).
